{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id79e33ae0-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s2215"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2215"},"text":"§ 2215.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Reports to Congress and President","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The Administrator of FEMA shall report to the Congress and the President not later than ninety calendar days following the year ending ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-09-30"},"text":"September 30, 1980","children":[],"tail":" and similarly each year thereafter on all activities relating to fire prevention and control, and all measures taken to implement and carry out this chapter during the preceding calendar year. Such report shall include, but need not be limited to—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id79e33ae1-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s2215/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a thorough appraisal, including statistical analysis, estimates, and long-term projections of the human and economic losses due to fire;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id79e33ae2-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s2215/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a survey and summary, in such detail as is deemed advisable, of the research and technology program undertaken or sponsored pursuant to this chapter;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id79e33ae3-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s2215/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" a summary of the activities of the Academy for the preceding 12 months, including, but not limited to—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id79e33ae4-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s2215/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" an explanation of the curriculum of study;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id79e33ae5-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s2215/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a description of the standards of admission and performance;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id79e33ae6-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s2215/c/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the criteria for the awarding of degrees and certificates; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id79e33ae7-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s2215/c/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a statistical compilation of the number of students attending the Academy and receiving degrees or certificates;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id79e33ae8-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s2215/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a summary of the activities undertaken to assist the Nation’s fire services;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id79e33ae9-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s2215/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a summary of the public education programs undertaken;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id79e33aea-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s2215/f"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"f"},"text":"(f)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" an analysis of the extent of participation in preparing and submitting Fire Safety Effectiveness Statements;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id79e33aeb-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s2215/g"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"g"},"text":"(g)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a summary of outstanding problems confronting the administration of this chapter, in order of priority;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id79e33aec-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s2215/h"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"h"},"text":"(h)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" such recommendations for additional legislation as are deemed necessary or appropriate; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id79e33aed-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s2215/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a summary of reviews, evaluations, and suggested improvements in State and local fire prevention and building codes, fire services, and any relevant Federal or private codes, regulations, and fire services.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id79e33aee-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/498/s16"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–498, § 16","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-10-29"},"text":"Oct. 29, 1974","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/88/1545"},"text":"88 Stat. 1545","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/472/tII/s202"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–472, title II, § 202","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-10-19"},"text":"Oct. 19, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/2260"},"text":"94 Stat. 2260","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/503/tI/s110/a/2/B/vi"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–503, title I, § 110(a)(2)(B)(vi)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-11-13"},"text":"Nov. 13, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/2302"},"text":"114 Stat. 2302","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/239/dA/tXVIII/s1802/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–239, div. A, title XVIII, § 1802(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2013-01-02"},"text":"Jan. 2, 2013","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/126/2100"},"text":"126 Stat. 2100","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id79e33aef-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id79e33af0-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id79e33af1-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This chapter, referred to in text, was in the original “this Act”, meaning ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/498"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–498","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-10-29"},"text":"Oct. 29, 1974","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/88/1535"},"text":"88 Stat. 1535","children":[],"tail":", which is classified principally to this chapter. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s2201"},"text":"section 2201 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id79e33af2-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2013—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/239"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–239","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Administrator of FEMA” for “Director” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2000—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/503"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–503","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Director” for “Secretary” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1980—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/472"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–472","children":[],"tail":" substituted “ninety calendar days following the year ending "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-09-30"},"text":"September 30, 1980","children":[],"tail":" and similarly each year thereafter” for “June 30 of the year following "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-10-29"},"text":"October 29, 1974","children":[],"tail":", and each year thereafter”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id79e33af3-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"id79e33af4-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For transfer of all functions, personnel, assets, components, authorities, grant programs, and liabilities of the Federal Emergency Management Agency, including the functions of the Under Secretary for Federal Emergency Management relating thereto, to the Federal Emergency Management Agency, see ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t6/s315/a/1"},"text":"section 315(a)(1) of Title 6","children":[],"tail":", Domestic Security."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For transfer of functions, personnel, assets, and liabilities of the Federal Emergency Management Agency, including the functions of the Director of the Federal Emergency Management Agency relating thereto, to the Secretary of Homeland Security, and for treatment of related references, see former section 313(1) and sections 551(d), 552(d), and 557 of Title 6, Domestic Security, and the Department of Homeland Security Reorganization Plan of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-11-25"},"text":"November 25, 2002","children":[],"tail":", as modified, set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t6/s542"},"text":"section 542 of Title 6","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"id79e33af5-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"id79e33af6-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Functions of National Fire Prevention and Control Administration [now United States Fire Administration] and National Academy for Fire Prevention and Control generally transferred to Federal Emergency Management Agency. For further details see Transfer of Functions note set out under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s2202"},"text":"section 2202 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
